PEDRO PEREZ pressed from inside early, could not keep pace with outer rivals and chased along the rail on the turn then two wide into the lane, stayed within striking range entering the final furlong but finished evenly late. BIG CHEDDAR fractious in the gate, raced up close three deep between rivals, got put in tight entering the turn, angled out and entered the lane five wide, then weakened in the lane. AROUND THE DIAL showed early speed but got put in tight between rivals and checked at the nine-sixteenths pole, chased three wide into the lane, angled out in the drive and lacked a rally. BOOMER JUSTICE raced up close then got put in tight entering the turn, chased three wide into the stretch and lacked a rally. MONGOLIAN BOX chased five wide into the turn, moved into the four path outside rivals then came six wide into the stretch and weakened. SPIRE dropped back off the pace, angled to the rail on the turn, tipped back out leaving the bend and could not make an impact.

MISCHELOF (CHI) took control from inside, dueled into and around the far turn, fought two wide into the lane and weakened.
